<p>Here’s the code (below) that you referenced but your code doesn’t match it. How come? How does the servo not work? If it does nothing, then you have the wrong port number or you didn’t copy the AndyMark code correctly (or never executed it).</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">Set Position (FRC):
The boundaries of the servo are different then the standard servo library.
https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/anyone-have-servo-example-code/155951/7
yourActuator = new Servo(RobotMap.YOUR_ACTUATOR_CHANNEL);
yourActuator.setBounds(2.0, 1.8, 1.5, 1.2, 1.0);
yourActuator.setSpeed(1.0); // to open
yourActuator.setSpeed(-1.0); // to close
</code></pre>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":4,"updated_at":"2025-04-02T19:54:22.866Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":12,"reads":81,"readers_count":80,"score":96.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":497847,"topic_slug":"linear-servo-programming-help","display_username":"SLAB-Mr.Thomas","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":24594,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/linear-servo-programming-help/497847/2","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3579585,"name":"Michael Jiang","username":"nmich","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/57b2e6/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-04-03T22:18:04.620Z","cooked":"<p>The function to set the bounds for wpi servos has changed for 2025, it’s now setBoundsMicroseconds. Ask you have to do is replace setBounds with that and multiply each parameter by 1000.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":4,"updated_at":"2025-04-03T22:18:04.620Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":39,"readers_count":38,"score":12.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":497847,"topic_slug":"linear-servo-programming-help","display_username":"Michael Jiang","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color"